==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tammy
<hw>Tam"my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tammies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of
woolen, or woolen and cotton, cloth, often highly glazed, -- used for
curtains, sieves, strainers, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sieve, or strainer, made of this material; a
tamis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tam-o'-shanter</ent>⟦br⟧
